SIMPLE: long-lived
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Long-lived
<hw>Long"-lived`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having a long life; having constitutional peculiarities which make
long life probable; lasting long; <as>as, a <ex>long-lived</ex> tree;
they are a <ex>long-lived</ex> family; <ex>long-lived</ex>
prejudices.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>same as <er>long-lasting</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> durable, lasting, long-lasting.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Longly</ent>⟦br⟧
